.TH git-commit-working 1  "git-commit-working " 
.SH NAME
git\-commit\-working \- Stage and commit working tree changes at specific paths
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgit\-commit\-working\fR [\fB\-n\fR|\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIPATHS\fR> [\fIPASSTHROUGH_ARGS\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Stages paths from working tree, then commits those staged changes.
.PP
This combines `git add paths` + `git commit\-staged paths` into one command.
.PP
Arguments after \-\- are passed through to git commit,
enabling \-m, \-\-amend, \-\-fixup, \-C, GPG signing, hooks, etc.
.PP
Examples:
  git commit\-working src/ \-\- \-m "Add feature"
  git commit\-working src/ tests/ \-\- \-\-amend
  git commit\-working . \-\- \-\-fixup HEAD~1
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Show what would be committed without committing
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIPATHS\fR>
Paths to stage and commit
.TP
[\fIPASSTHROUGH_ARGS\fR]
Arguments to pass through to git commit
